        public int getPair(int baseIndex)
        Returns -1 if the given index does not belong to this structure element or if it is not paired. Otherwise, returns the index of the base that is paired with the base at the given index.

      • getTextRegion

        public int getTextRegion(int[] regions)
        A client calls with with an already-created array of integers. The StructItem must fill it with a list of text regions from which the element was created. Each region occupies two elements in the array: the start and stop positions (inclusive) in the text.
        Parameters:
        regions - an already-instantiated array of integers to receive the text regions.
        Returns:
        The number of regions that were filled.
